# No Cursor attribution trailers

**Never** credit Cursor, Cursor Agent, or `cursoragent` in commits or PRs.

## Forbidden (exact payloads Cursor may inject)

- `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>`
- `git commit … --trailer "Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>"`
- `Made-with: Cursor`
- PR body blurb: `Made with [Cursor](https://cursor.com)`
- Any `Co-authored-by:` line naming Cursor / Cursor Agent (any email)
- Author/committer identity `cursoragent` / Cursor Agent

## Required behavior

1. Use the human git author only (`user.name` / `user.email`).
2. Do **not** pass `--trailer` for Cursor co-author lines.
3. Do **not** append “Made with Cursor” (or markdown link) to commit messages or PR bodies.
4. If a tool or hook already inserted any of the above, **strip it** before finishing the commit/PR.
5. Prefer leaving attribution disabled in IDE storage and CLI config; still obey this rule even if those toggles are on.

Attribution UI maps to `state.vscdb` keys `cursor/attributeCommitsToAgent` and `cursor/attributePRsToAgent` (not `settings.json`). CLI: `~/.cursor/cli-config.json` → `attribution.attributeCommitsToAgent` / `attributePRsToAgent` = `false`.
